commit.message: of course let stuff depending on 'warp' accept the new version
warp: don't use 'ByteString.Builder' for 'push', as it's twice as slow, and some more tweaks to improve performance
warp/bench: added benchmark for 'headerLines' to see if we're making things better or worse
warp: adjusted 'Request.hs' to build with 'bytestring < 0.11' and removed 'BangPatterns'

warp/test: adjusted tests to confirm that multiline headers are not supported anymore

I checked the parsing of headers functions and we apparently do not throw or abort
on any invalid header formats. Do we want to do that? Or do we defer that judgement
to any user of 'warp'?
warp: removed checking for multiline headers and inlined a few things
warp/test: rewrote some tests and added a stupid but valid one too
warp/test: calculate length instead of hardcoding
